1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:04,919
Hi and welcome to The Winning Factor. I'm Alan Aitken, and on this show each week

2
00:00:04,919 --> 00:00:10,259
we take a look at some upcoming races in Hong Kong, try to identify an angle to

3
00:00:10,259 --> 00:00:15,120
The race that might lead us to finding the winner. Well, it's Saturday racing.

4
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:19,820
this weekend in Hong Kong, the first race I'm going to take a look at is Race

5
00:00:19,820 --> 00:00:25,679
Ten, where our winning factor is the map. So this is Class 3, 1600 metres.

6
00:00:25,679 --> 00:00:29,259
And Blazing Wukong and Amazing Partners are coming off last start wins.

7
00:00:29,820 --> 00:00:33,140
Endured has been racing well in similar events without much luck.

8
00:00:33,679 --> 00:00:35,920
Smart Avenue should improve with a better draw.

9
00:00:36,380 --> 00:00:40,539
And Family Jewel and Hymnbook both look to have chances as well.

10
00:00:41,439 --> 00:00:44,460
So not a one-horse race by any means.

11
00:00:44,579 --> 00:00:45,560
Quite a few chances.

12
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:53,920
But I'm looking most closely at a couple of horses I think will cope with what looks quite a tricky event in terms of the map.

13
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:57,380
And that's Blazing Wukong and Amazing Partners.

14
00:00:58,219 --> 00:01:01,539
Now, Amazing Partners, first of all, well, he's lightly raced.

15
00:01:01,679 --> 00:01:03,880
He's only had six starts for three wins.

16
00:01:04,379 --> 00:01:08,439
And this was his latest when he tackled 1,600 metres for the first time.

17
00:01:08,859 --> 00:01:12,200
This is Race 601. He's in gate four, pink colours.

18
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:16,200
And Amazing Partners jumps well. He isn't a quick horse naturally.

19
00:01:16,740 --> 00:01:20,280
But Vincent Ho is able to get him into a position near the lead.

20
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:22,960
through what is a slow first sectional

21
00:01:22,959 --> 00:01:26,759
Before the pace does pick up a little through the middle stages.

22
00:01:26,939 --> 00:01:28,919
but still is only steady.

23
00:01:29,759 --> 00:01:32,099
A number of Saturday's rivals are here too.

24
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:34,539
In Jude, inside amazing partners in red and grey.

25
00:01:34,679 --> 00:01:37,759
Mr Dapper, the leader, and Himbuk in green near the tail.

26
00:01:37,839 --> 00:01:41,239
Now, the field is bunched here with no serious pace.

27
00:01:41,239 --> 00:01:44,039
and becomes just a dash down the straight

28
00:01:44,539 --> 00:01:46,459
With Endue on the inside having no luck.

29
00:01:46,780 --> 00:01:49,280
But amazing partners, well, he's able to be challenging

30
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,959
at the right time with enough turn of foot

31
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:54,739
to reel in the leaders and he grinds out the win.

32
00:01:56,299 --> 00:02:00,579
Now, despite his good winning record, three from six amazing partners

33
00:02:00,839 --> 00:02:03,579
I don't really think we've seen the best of him yet

34
00:02:03,579 --> 00:02:06,619
because he's been in several of these kinds of races

35
00:02:06,619 --> 00:02:09,459
where it's just a grinding sort of finish

36
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,759
difficult to get separation on the field.

37
00:02:11,879 --> 00:02:15,219
So he's done well to put that record together

38
00:02:15,219 --> 00:02:19,620
and that could be a key thing in Saturday's race.

39
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:21,219
Now, Blazing Wukong, on the other hand,

40
00:02:21,219 --> 00:02:26,340
He's a little bit more well explored with 11 starts so far for three wins.

41
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,159
And here's his latest offering.

42
00:02:28,379 --> 00:02:32,020
This is race 643, gate 13 in black colours.

43
00:02:32,199 --> 00:02:40,360
And Blazing Wukong jumps okay, but jockey Andrea Zanido doesn't even think of looking for a more forward position going back to the rear.

44
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:43,360
Now, that prevents him covering extra ground early.

45
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:49,219
But we can see on the heat map it's also a disadvantage with the slow early speed here.

46
00:02:49,219 --> 00:02:54,219
The pace is a little better mid-race but never really gets above steady.

47
00:02:54,219 --> 00:02:59,039
Blazing Wukong then sprints well around the field, deceptively fast around the field in

48
00:02:59,039 --> 00:03:03,539
In fact, as they turn into the stretch, he's the one with the acceleration to go and pick.

49
00:03:03,539 --> 00:03:06,719
up the leaders and put them away.

50
00:03:06,719 --> 00:03:12,780
Just like Amazing Partners, not the most impressive win to the eye but what they have in common.

51
00:03:12,780 --> 00:03:19,120
is that each of them had to produce acceleration at the right time, the right place to go and

52
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:24,800
win the race and as I said I think that's going to be important in the context of Saturday's race.

53
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:31,379
Now the leaders, Mr. Dapper and With All My Faith, have the outside gates, so that is the hope of the...

54
00:03:31,379 --> 00:03:37,980
side as far as getting a better speed, but it's quite possible they could get across quickly and

55
00:03:37,980 --> 00:03:43,420
then steady the brakes and we might have a similar style of race to what we've been seeing.

56
00:03:43,419 --> 00:03:49,599
There still looks a little speed in it, inside or out, and that's not going to help the likes

57
00:03:49,599 --> 00:03:55,979
of Family Jewel, Endured and others who have wider draws, while Hymnbook and Smart Avenue

58
00:03:55,979 --> 00:04:01,479
have never really shown as much tactical speed yet, regardless of their draw.

59
00:04:01,479 --> 00:04:04,000
Now Blazing Wukong went all the way back last time.

60
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:10,279
We have seen him ridden like that quite a bit, but he has also had a lot of wider draws.

61
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:15,439
This time he's got a better draw, so he might even be closer from Barrier Five.

62
00:04:15,439 --> 00:04:20,279
But we do know that Amazing Partners has the tactical speed to be where he needs to be.

63
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:22,220
be again.

64
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:27,540
So the tip from me in race 10, Amazing Partners, his winning factor, the map.

65
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:32,199
It does look a very tricky map, but it could be a stop-start kind of race.

66
00:04:32,199 --> 00:04:37,340
But what we've seen from Amazing Partners, even in those kinds of races, is that he's

67
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:39,500
able to put himself in the right place. He's

68
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:47,680
able to accelerate at the right time and that might be the winning recipe for this event.

69
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:51,819
The other race I want to take a look at on Sunday is the final event, race 11 and our

70
00:04:51,819 --> 00:04:53,779
winning factor here, the draw.

71
00:04:53,779 --> 00:04:59,620
This is Class Two, an excellent Class Two in fact, over 1200 metres and despite the

72
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:05,620
Talent in the Race, I think we can narrow this down to three really strong chances.

73
00:05:05,620 --> 00:05:07,879
Patch of Stars, who continues to race well.

74
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:12,759
and two horses we expect to see figuring in some serious races in the future.

75
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:17,519
Jamie Richards' trained Bulb General and the unbeaten three-year-old Hot Delight.

76
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:22,620
And I'm most interested in this race in those two lightly raced horses.

77
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:25,579
As I said, Hot Delight, unbeaten, three from three.

78
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:30,519
and Bulb General, a year older, and he's three wins from five starts.

79
00:05:31,259 --> 00:05:34,459
Now, firstly, Hot Delight, and his trainer, Francis Loy,

80
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:40,219
has made comparisons at the same stage with a horse that you might be familiar with that he

81
00:05:40,219 --> 00:05:46,019
used to train Golden Sixty. That's a big call. Certainly there's a lot of water to flow under

82
00:05:46,019 --> 00:05:52,899
the bridge for that one, but he can't be faulted in what he's done so far. This is race 540. He's

83
00:05:52,899 --> 00:05:59,259
in gate seven in yellow and red colours, and Hot Delight jumps well for Vincent Ho and is quickly

84
00:05:59,259 --> 00:06:06,159
Up on the speed, in what you can see is a slow first 400-metre section with Ho on the odds.

85
00:06:06,159 --> 00:06:09,800
on favourite here taking bad luck out of the equation.

86
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:15,240
Now the pace does lift a little as the race progresses then becomes a strong sprint home.

87
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:16,579
down the stretch.

88
00:06:16,579 --> 00:06:21,599
The leader fights on well but ultimately Hot Delight is too good and comes clear to win.

89
00:06:21,599 --> 00:06:23,879
with some conviction.

90
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:28,939
Now, perhaps to the eye, not deserving the kind of boom that we're talking about on this horse.

91
00:06:28,939 --> 00:06:33,600
But the way the race was run there meant that to win it the way he did,

92
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:37,839
Hot Delight had to break 44 seconds for his last 800 metres.

93
00:06:37,839 --> 00:06:42,420
And that's the kind of sustained speed that is going to make this young horse.

94
00:06:42,420 --> 00:06:47,060
A star of the future as he develops and grows stronger.

95
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:50,899
As to Bold General, well, as I mentioned, he's a year older.

96
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:56,779
And really, he was this time last year where Hot Delight is now.

97
00:06:57,239 --> 00:07:02,239
He was an up-and-comer with a great turn of foot as a three-year-old.

98
00:07:02,459 --> 00:07:04,959
He took that into his early starts as a four-year-old.

99
00:07:05,039 --> 00:07:08,579
but then his career was interrupted by injury.

100
00:07:09,259 --> 00:07:11,719
He's only had the one run back in March.

101
00:07:12,039 --> 00:07:14,479
and let's have a look at how he handled that.

102
00:07:14,739 --> 00:07:18,699
This is Race 562, gate seven here in orange and white colours.

103
00:07:19,039 --> 00:07:21,339
Bulb General jumps well for Zac Purton.

104
00:07:21,759 --> 00:07:24,419
but this race is a contrast with the one that we just saw

105
00:07:24,479 --> 00:07:26,479
as the early speed here is pretty good.

106
00:07:26,779 --> 00:07:32,719
Zak let Bulb General find his feet as is usual, and he ends up towards the rear with

107
00:07:32,719 --> 00:07:37,319
another of Saturday's rivals Patch of Stars in yellow, white and blue a few lengths ahead

108
00:07:37,319 --> 00:07:38,879
of him on the rail.

109
00:07:38,879 --> 00:07:44,619
Now the pace increases again mid-race so it's really run to suit horses off the pace.

110
00:07:44,619 --> 00:07:49,059
When they straighten up, Patch of Stars comes to pounce; he comes up short behind Young.

111
00:07:49,059 --> 00:07:53,779
Champion with Bob General working home steadily into third.

112
00:07:53,779 --> 00:08:00,059
Now Bob General will meet the first two that beat him home there on Saturday, but they

113
00:08:00,059 --> 00:08:05,539
were hard race-fit horses and he was coming off quite a lengthy break.

114
00:08:05,539 --> 00:08:11,159
So I do think he's going to tighten up and be a better version of himself on Saturday.

115
00:08:11,159 --> 00:08:16,839
But I think when we go to the draw, that's where things are really getting interesting.

116
00:08:16,839 --> 00:08:18,199
in this race.

117
00:08:18,199 --> 00:08:22,459
There's good speed out wide here from Victor the winner, Crimson Flash and Lady's Choice.

118
00:08:22,459 --> 00:08:24,099
So the tempo looks sound enough.

119
00:08:24,099 --> 00:08:28,599
Bob General is drawn lower this time, while he's still not going to be on the front end.

120
00:08:28,599 --> 00:08:29,599
of the race.

121
00:08:29,599 --> 00:08:34,559
His jockey this time, Joe Moreira, should be able to use that draw to get a nice trip.

122
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:36,159
through the race.

123
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:40,819
Harry Bentley takes over on Hot Delight with the light weight, but his map looks filled.

124
00:08:40,819 --> 00:08:45,360
with a lot of decisions to make, and tough ones they are.

125
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:49,899
We saw Hot Delight up on the speed, his last two starts in slow tempos, but with a better

126
00:08:49,899 --> 00:08:55,500
pace and a wide draw here he would have trouble getting to a similar spot without covering ground

127
00:08:55,500 --> 00:09:01,019
and working and might even have to drag all the way back in the field so that he doesn't have a

128
00:09:01,019 --> 00:09:09,100
difficult run, so the tip from me in race 11 is Bulb General. His winning factor, the draw now had they

129
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:15,419
Drawn the other way around, I'm sure that I would have been tipping Hot Delight, but his job looks

130
00:09:15,419 --> 00:09:19,379
full of difficulties. He's good enough to overcome them. I certainly don't want to

131
00:09:19,379 --> 00:09:23,819
say it's lights out for his chances but it brings him back to the older horse

132
00:09:23,819 --> 00:09:28,500
who has drawn better this time, Bold General, and should be fitter than he was

133
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:34,199
for that first up run. Well, that's it from The Winning Factor this week. Good

134
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:38,059
luck on Saturday. We'll see you next time.
